<emphasis box="[941,1110,1765,1788]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. constanciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by having a pungent opercular spine (Okamoto 2012). This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Barnard" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[834,962,1800,1824]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis box="[834,962,1800,1824]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having 11 + 14 vertebrae; however, it differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Barnard" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[297,426,1836,1860]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis box="[297,426,1836,1860]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in orbital diameter longer than postorbital length (
<figureCitation box="[1015,1099,1836,1861]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="16.[151,250,701,723]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,267,679]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[188,1398,267,679]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 12. Epigonus lenimen, MNHN 1989-1121, 1 of 2 specimens, 108.6 mm SL." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1182193/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) (vs. orbital diameter shorter than postorbital length in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Barnard" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[446,574,1872,1896]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis box="[446,574,1872,1896]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and in lacking two nub-like structures on the symphysis of lower jaw (vs. present in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Barnard" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[272,400,1908,1932]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis box="[272,400,1908,1932]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The other 5 species of the group in the 
<collectingRegion box="[883,974,1909,1932]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="Western" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">Western</collectingRegion>
Indian Ocean, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Okamoto &amp; Gon" authorityYear="2018" box="[1151,1302,1908,1932]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bispinosus">
<emphasis box="[1151,1302,1908,1932]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. bispinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Okamoto &amp; Gon" authorityYear="2018" box="[1319,1396,1908,1932]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="idai">
<emphasis box="[1319,1396,1908,1932]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. idai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Parin &amp; Abramov" authorityYear="1986" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marimonticolus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. marimonticolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mayer" authorityYear="1974" box="[340,480,1944,1968]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pectinifer">
<emphasis box="[340,480,1944,1968]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. pectinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Parin &amp; Abramov" authorityYear="1986" box="[533,702,1944,1968]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="waltersensis">
<emphasis box="[533,702,1944,1968]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. waltersensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, have 10 + 15 vertebrae (vs. 11 + 
<quantity box="[1085,1142,1943,1968]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.556" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" unit="in" value="14.0">14 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scott" authorityYear="1962" box="[1149,1269,1944,1968]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lenimen">
<emphasis box="[1149,1269,1944,1968]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. lenimen</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="277" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1007,2005]" box="[199,1436,1980,2005]" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scott" authorityYear="1962" box="[199,400,1980,2004]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lenimen">
<emphasis box="[199,400,1980,2004]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">Epigonus lenimen</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is originally described based on 
<typeStatus box="[766,864,1980,2005]" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">holotype</typeStatus>
and nine 
<typeStatus box="[973,1080,1981,2005]" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">paratypes</typeStatus>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1148,1250,1980,2005]" name="Australia" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">Australia</collectingCountry>
(Whitley 1935).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,151,213]" pageId="16" pageNumber="277">
According to a re-examination of Whitley’s 
<typeStatus box="[675,723,152,176]" pageId="16" pageNumber="277">type</typeStatus>
series by 
<bibRefCitation box="[849,1011,152,176]" pageId="16" pageNumber="277" refId="ref20071" refString="Mayer, G. F. (1974) A revision of the cardinalfish genus Epigonus (Perciformes, Apogonidae), with descriptions of two new species. Bulletin Museum of Comparative Zoology, 146, 147 - 203." type="journal article">Mayer (1974)</bibRefCitation>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[1073,1180,152,176]" pageId="16" pageNumber="277">paratypes</typeStatus>
were identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dieuzeide" authorityYear="1950" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="277" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="denticulatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="277">E. denticulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in his revision of the genus.
</paragraph>
